summary:
In the Department of Bio-Organic Chemistry at Utrecht University (1969-2009), over the years a multidisciplinary carbohydrate research program has been carried out that combined:
(A) Primary / 3D structural analysis of microbial and plant oligo/polysaccharides, (recombinant) glycoprotein glycans, and oligosaccharides from physiological fluids.
(B) Chemical / enzymatic synthesis of oligosaccharide fragments of microbial polysaccharides,  glycopeptides, and glycoprotein glycans.
(C) Carbohydrate-protein and carbohydrate-carbohydrate interaction studies.

Research themes were related to biomedical/pharmaceutical and food-technological/rheological problems.
